# Vanessa Braganholo

Full Professor (Prof. Titular) - [Instituto de Computação](http://www.ic.uff.br) <BR/>
[Universidade Federal Fluminense](http://www.uff.br), Niterói, RJ, Brazil.

## Short Bio

Vanessa Braganholo is a Full Professor at the [Instituto de Computação](http://www.ic.uff.br) of Universidade Federal Fluminense ([UFF](http://www.uff.br)) since 2010. Before that, she worked as an Assistant Professor at Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro ([UFRJ](http://www.dcc.ufrj.br)). She holds a Ph.D. (2004) and a B.S. (1998) degree in Computer Science from Universidade Federal do Rio Grande do Sul ([UFRGS](http://www.inf.ufrgs.br)). She received the Best PhD Thesis Award of the Brazilian Computer Society in 2005. She has a productivity research grant level 2 from [CNPq](http://www.cnpq.br) since 2007 and had a Young Scientist research grant from [FAPERJ](http://www.faperj.br) from 2010 to 2016. She has published over 100 papers in journals and conferences. She is the PC Co-Chair of [EDBT 2026](https://edbticdt2026.github.io/). She has served as PC Chair (CIKM Workshops Chair, SIGMOD Jim Gray Dissertation Award 2022 and 2021, IPAW 2021 and 2020, PVLDB DEMO 2018, SBBD 2018, SIGMOD DEMO 2015) and as a program committee member of several conferences such as VLDB, MSR, ICDE, CIKM, IPAW, SBBD, and TaPP. She serves as the editor of the Distinguished Database Profiles of SIGMOD RECORD since 2011. Her research area is databases, and her current research interests include databases and provenance.

